<script>
    var MOUSE_DWELL = 750; // millisecond delay for mouse enter/leave events to take effect

    mapboxgl.accessToken = 'pk.eyJ1IjoiY2hwZGIiLCJhIjoiY2pxemUwY3p5MDBzNzRhbnpycnNobmd1NCJ9.PXPeEfqL69uM5l1AY5FINQ';
    var map = new mapboxgl.Map({
        container: 'map',
        style: 'mapbox://styles/chpdb/cjqze90kn10o52snsiebb9hwe',
        center: [-95.97692937483515, 38.6926067289518],
        zoom: 3.4,
        maxBounds: [[-125.72414338579958, 21.357002122461935], [-66.22971536386672, 52.66337225178401]],
        hash: false
    });
    map.addControl(new mapboxgl.NavigationControl());
    map.on('load', function () {
        map.addSource('microgrids', {
            'type': 'geojson',
            'data': '/microgrids/index'
        });
        map.addLayer({
            'id': 'microgrid_markers',
            'type': "circle",
            'source': 'microgrids',
            'paint': {
                // make circles larger as the user zooms from z12 to z22
                'circle-radius': {
                    'base': 1.0,
                    'property': 'capacity',
                    //'stops': [[1,3], [10,4], [100,5], [1000,6], [10000,7], [100000,8], [1000000,9], [10000000,10], [100000000,11]]
                    'stops': circle_radii()
                },
                'circle-color': "#66a666",
                'circle-opacity': {
                    'base': 1.0,
                    'property': 'capacity',
                    'stops': [[1,1.0], [10,.92], [100,.86], [1000,.78], [10000,.70], [100000,.62], [1000000,.54], [10000000,.46], [100000000,.38]],
                }
            }
        });
    });

    function circle_radii() {
        var radii = [];
        var steps = [1,10,100,1000,10000,100000,1000000,10000000,100000000];
        for (var zoom = 1; zoom < 23; zoom += 2) {
            for (var step = 0; step < steps.length; step++) {
                radii.push([{zoom: zoom, value: steps[step]}, 2 + ((step + 1) * (zoom + 2) / 8)])
            }
        }
        return radii;
    }

    var popup = new mapboxgl.Popup({
        closeButton: true,
        closeOnClick: true
    });

    function show_popup(feature) {
        var coordinates = feature.geometry.coordinates.slice();
        var facilityName = feature.properties.projectName;
        var organizationName = feature.properties.organizationName;
        var application = feature.properties.application;
        var capacityStr = feature.properties.capacityStr;
        var primeMover = feature.properties.primeMover;
        var technologies = eval(feature.properties.technologies);
        var state = feature.properties.state;
        var href = BASE_URL + 'state/microgrid/' + state + '?f=' + feature.properties.id;
        var badges = "";
        for (let tech of technologies) {
            switch (tech) {
                case 'Solar':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-solar"><span title="Solar" class="pill-content">PV</span></span>';
                    break;
                case 'Wind':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-wind"><span title="Wind" class="pill-content">W</span></span>';
                    break;
                case 'Hydro':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-hydro"><span title="Hydro" class="pill-content">H</span></span>';
                    break;
                case 'Fuel Cell':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-fuelcell"><span title="Fuel Cell" class="pill-content">FC</span></span>';
                    break
                case 'Diesel':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-diesel"><span title="Non-CHP Diesel" class="pill-content">DSL</span></span>';
                    break;
                case 'Biogas':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-biogas"><span title="Non-CHP Biogas" class="pill-content">BG</span></span>';
                    break;
                case 'Natural Gas':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-natgas"><span title="Non-CHP Natural Gas" class="pill-content">NG</span></span>';
                    break;
                case 'CHP':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-chp"><span title="CHP" class="pill-content">CHP</span></span>';
                    break;
                case 'Storage':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-storage"><span title="Storage" class="pill-content">STG</span></span>';
                    break;
                
                
                
                case 'Controls':
                case 'Advanced Controls':
                    badges += '<span class="pill pill-advanced-controls"><span title="Advanced Microgrid Controls" class="pill-content">MCTRL</span></span>';
                    break;
            }
        }
        var html = "<div class=\"microgrid-marker-popup-title\"><h3>"
            + "<a href=\"" + href + "\">" + facilityName + "</a>"
            + "</h3></div>"
            + "<div style='float:right; padding-top: 2.0em;'>" + badges + "</div>"
            + "<p style=\"padding-top:1.0em\"><b>Organization Name</b><br/>" + organizationName + "</p>"
            + "<p><b>Application</b><br/>" + application + "</p>"
            + "<p><b>Capacity (kW)</b><br/>" + capacityStr + "</p>"
        // if (projectProfileLink) {
        //     html += "<div><a href=\"" + projectProfileLink + "\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">Project profile</a></div>";
        // }
        popup.setLngLat(coordinates)
            .setHTML(html)
            .addTo(map);
    }

    function hide_popup() {
        if (popup.isOpen()) {
            popup.remove();
        }
    }

    var popup_enter_timer = null;

    // Change the cursor to a pointer when the mouse is over the places layer.
    map.on('mouseenter', 'microgrid_markers', function (e) {
        map.getCanvas().style.cursor = 'pointer';
        if (popup_enter_timer) {
            window.clearTimeout(popup_enter_timer);
            popup_enter_timer = null;
        }
        popup_enter_timer = window.setTimeout(function () {
                show_popup(e.features[0]);
            },
            MOUSE_DWELL);
    });

    // Change it back to a pointer when it leaves.
    map.on('mouseleave', 'microgrid_markers', function () {
        map.getCanvas().style.cursor = '';
        if (popup_enter_timer) {
            window.clearTimeout(popup_enter_timer);
            popup_enter_timer = null;
        }
    });

    map.on('click', 'microgrid_markers', function (e) {
        if (popup_enter_timer) {
            window.clearTimeout(popup_enter_timer);
            popup_enter_timer = null;
        }
        show_popup(e.features[0]);
    });

    $("#map1 a").click(function () {
        map.setMaxBounds([[-125.72414338579958, 21.357002122461935], [-66.22971536386672, 52.66337225178401]]);
        map.setMaxZoom(22);
        map.setZoom(3.4);
        map.panTo([-95.97692937483515, 38.6926067289518]);
        $(".map-regions li").removeClass('active');
        $(this).parents('li').addClass('active');
        return false;
    });
    $("#map2 a").click(function () {
        //map.setMaxBounds([[-195.45618924951592, 49.69692710516631], [-120.85349250180701, 72.72541486937857]]);
        map.setMaxBounds([[-195.45618924951592, 49.69692710516631], [-120.85349250180701, 72.72541486937857]]);
        map.setMaxZoom(4.4);
        map.setZoom(3.1317841252919703);
        map.panTo([-158.15484087566358 + 360, 63.43150356149306]);
        $(".map-regions li").removeClass('active');
        $(this).parents('li').addClass('active');
        return false;
    });
    $("#map3 a").click(function () {
        map.setMaxBounds([[-162.69528066317892, 16.83252756574697], [-151.29559341555282, 24.062198519305568]]);
        map.setMaxZoom(22);
        map.setZoom(5.842017663090445);
        map.panTo([-156.99543703936445, 20.48995480493666]);
        $(".map-regions li").removeClass('active');
        $(this).parents('li').addClass('active');
        return false;
    });
    $("#map4 a").click(function () {
        map.setMaxBounds([[-67.38064932077728, 17.089526423415634], [-64.12896622092912, 19.182704689623023]]);
        map.setMaxZoom(22);
        map.setZoom(7.651753339179141);
        map.panTo([-65.75480777085306, 18.139246961979197]);
        $(".map-regions li").removeClass('active');
        $(this).parents('li').addClass('active');
        return false;
    });

    

    $("#application").on('change', function () {
        applyMapFilter();
    });

    $("#technology").on("change", function () {
        applyMapFilter();
    });

    $('#grid_type').on('change', function() {
       applyMapFilter();
    });

    $('#filter-reset').on('click', function() {
       $('#application').val('all');
       $('#technology').val('all');
       $('#grid_type').val('all');
       applyMapFilter();
    });

    function applyMapFilter() {
        var technology = $("#technology option:selected").text();
        var application = $("#application option:selected").text();
        var grid_type = $("#grid_type option:selected").text();
        hide_popup();
        if (technology === "All Technologies" && application === "All Applications" && grid_type === "All Types") {
            map.setFilter("microgrid_markers", null);
        } else {
            var filter = ["all"];
            if (application !== "All Applications") {
                filter.push(["==", "application", application]);
            }
            if (grid_type !== "All Types") {
                filter.push(["==", "grid_type", grid_type]);
            }
            if (technology !== "All Technologies") {
                switch (technology) {
                    case "CHP": filter.push(["==", "tech_chp", true]); break;
                    case "Biogas": filter.push(["==", "tech_biogas", true]); break;
                    case "Diesel": filter.push(["==", "tech_diesel", true]); break;
                    case "Fuel Cell": filter.push(["==", "tech_fuelcell", true]); break;
                    case "Hydro": filter.push(["==", "tech_hydro", true]); break;
                    case "Natural Gas": filter.push(["==", "tech_natgas", true]); break;
                    case "Solar": filter.push(["==", "tech_solar", true]); break;
                    case "Storage": filter.push(["==", "tech_storage", true]); break;
                    case "Wind": filter.push(["==", "tech_wind", true]); break;
                    case "Advanced Controls": filter.push(["==", "tech_controls", true]); break;
                }
                // // filter.push(["in", technology, ["get","technologies"]]);
                // filter.push([">=", ["index-of", technology, ["get","technologies"]], 0]);
            }
            map.setFilter("microgrid_markers", filter, {validate: true});
        }
    }

    $(function () {
        // Pressing the browser's back button should not partially restore prior state
        $("#application option").prop("selected", false);
    });
</script>

            <div style="margin-top: 1em;">
                <div class="twelve-columns" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 16px; vertical-align: top;">
                    <div class="map-legend-descrip">

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top: 1em;">
                <div class="twelve-columns" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 16px; vertical-align: top;">
                    A microgrid is a network of distributed energy resources and loads that can disconnect and re-connect
                    to the larger utility grid as a single entity, allowing the connected loads to be served during
                    utility outages. Microgrids can also be found in remote locations where they may not be connected to
                    a larger grid. Some standby/backup generators are configured to connect/disconnect and operate
                    independently from the utility grid during an outage but these backup generators are not included in
                    the database unless they are part of a microgrid that serves other functions, such as daily power
                    requirements or participation in utility markets.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

from collections import Counter

# Flatten the list of technologies and count the occurrences of each technology
tech_counts = Counter([tech.lower() for sublist in gdf['technologies'] for tech in sublist])

# Now 'tech_counts' is a dictionary where the keys are the technologies and the values are their counts

import requests
import json

# API endpoint for the microgrid data
api_url = 'https://doe.icfwebservices.com/microgrids/index'

# Send a GET request to the API
response = requests.get(api_url)

response
<Response [200]>
# Check if the request was successful
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Load the JSON data
    data = response.json()
    
    # Now you can work with the JSON data
    # For example, print the first microgrid's information
    if data and isinstance(data, list) and len(data) > 0:
        print(f"First microgrid's information: {data[0]}")

        print('No data found or unexpected data format.')
else:
